<DOC><DOCNO> AP880405-0150 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-04-05-88 1540EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r i AM-BRF--Ghana     04-05 0135</FIRST><SECOND>AM-BRF--Ghana,0142</SECOND><HEAD>Three Cabinet Members Lose Jobs in Ghana</HEAD><DATELINE>ACCRA, Ghana (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Three cabinet members in this West Africannation have been replaced in a shake-up, an official communiquesaid Tuesday.   The statement, read on national radio, said secretaries formobilization and social welfare, works and housing, and health weredismissed.   The communique gave no reason for the changes, and it did notsay if the secretaries would be moved to others jobs.   The country's leader, Flight Lt. Jerry Rawlings, has beencracking down on official corruption. Authorities fired 33 policeofficers a week ago and 19 others two weeks earlier, accusing themof drug trafficking, armed robbery, and accepting bribes.   In other changes announced Tuesday, several secretaries in thecabinet, known as the Provisional National Defense Council, weremoved to other posts.</TEXT></DOC>